{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Real-Time Sales Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "**Kafka (EC2) → Databricks (PySpark Structured Streaming) → S3 (raw/bronze) → DynamoDB (aggregated/silver)**\n",
    "\n",
    "Architecture overview:\n",
    "- Ingest real-time sales events from Kafka\n",
    "- Parse JSON → structure data\n",
    "- Save raw events (bronze layer)\n",
    "- Aggregate by product/category\n",
    "- Write summarized data to DynamoDB tables (one per category)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Read Streaming Data from Kafka"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = (\n",
    "    spark.readStream\n",
    "    .format(\"kafka\")\n",
    "    .option(\"kafka.bootstrap.servers\", \"43.205.136.148:9092\")\n",
    "    .option(\"subscribe\", \"test-topic\")\n",
    "    .option(\"startingOffsets\", \"earliest\")           # or \"latest\" for new data only\n",
    "    .option(\"failOnDataLoss\", \"false\")\n",
    "    .load()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Expected schema: key, value (binary), topic, partition, offset, timestamp, ..."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Extract value as JSON string"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pyspark.sql.functions import col\n",
    "\n",
    "json_string_df = df.selectExpr(\"CAST(value AS STRING) AS json_data\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Define schema & parse JSON"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pyspark.sql.functions import from_json\n",
    "from pyspark.sql.types import *\n",
    "\n",
    "schema = StructType([\n",
    "    StructField(\"sale_id\",       IntegerType(), True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"order_id\",      StringType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"customer_id\",   StringType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"product_id\",    StringType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"product_name\",  StringType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"category\",      StringType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"quantity\",      IntegerType(), True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"unit_price\",    DoubleType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"total_amount\",  DoubleType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"sale_date\",     StringType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"payment_method\",StringType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"region\",        StringType(),  True),\n",
    "    StructField(\"created_at\",    StringType(),  True)\n",
    "])\n",
    "\n",
    "parsed_df = (\n",
    "    json_string_df\n",
    "    .select(from_json(col(\"json_data\"), schema).alias(\"data\"))\n",
    "    .select(\"data.*\")\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Write raw data to local storage (Bronze layer workaround)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note**: Databricks Community Edition has restrictions — direct streaming write to S3 often requires Unity Catalog external locations or paid features.  \n",
    "→ We write to `/tmp` or `/FileStore` as workaround. You can later copy to S3 manually or use Jobs/Auto Loader in production."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "raw_query = (\n",
    "    parsed_df\n",
    "    .writeStream\n",
    "    .format(\"json\")\n",
    "    .option(\"path\", \"/tmp/kafka_raw_sales\")           # or \"/FileStore/tables/bronze_sales\"\n",
    "    .option(\"checkpointLocation\", \"/tmp/checkpoints/bronze\")\n",
    "    .outputMode(\"append\")\n",
    "    .trigger(processingTime=\"30 seconds\")             # adjust as needed\n",
    "    .start()\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# raw_query.awaitTermination()   # uncomment to block notebook"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Aggregate data (Silver layer preparation)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pyspark.sql.functions import sum as sum_\n",
    "\n",
    "agg_df = (\n",
    "    parsed_df\n",
    "    .groupBy(\"product_id\", \"product_name\", \"category\")\n",
    "    .agg(\n",
    "        sum_(\"quantity\").alias(\"total_quantity\"),\n",
    "        sum_(\"total_amount\").alias(\"total_revenue\")\n",
    "    )\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 6. Split by category (for separate DynamoDB tables)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "electronics_df = agg_df.filter(\"category = 'Electronics'\")\n",
    "accessories_df = agg_df.filter(\"category = 'Accessories'\")\n",
    "furniture_df   = agg_df.filter(\"category = 'Furniture'\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 7. Convert streaming aggregations to static for DynamoDB\n",
    "\n",
    "**Note**: DynamoDB write via boto3 requires static DataFrame → we use `.toPandas()` after collecting micro-batch results (demo only — not production scale)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# For demo: collect current aggregation state\n",
    "electronics_pd = electronics_df.writeStream \\\n",
    "    .outputMode(\"complete\") \\\n",
    "    .format(\"memory\") \\\n",
    "    .queryName(\"electronics_agg\") \\\n",
    "    .start()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Wait a bit, then read from in-memory table\n",
    "spark.sql(\"SELECT * FROM electronics_agg\").show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. DynamoDB Setup & Type-safe Insert"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import boto3\n",
    "from decimal import Decimal\n",
    "\n",
    "dynamodb = boto3.resource(\n",
    "    'dynamodb',\n",
    "    aws_access_key_id     = \"YOUR_ACCESS_KEY\",\n",
    "    aws_secret_access_key = \"YOUR_SECRET_KEY\",\n",
    "    region_name           = \"ap-south-1\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "def convert_value(v):\n",
    "    if isinstance(v, float):\n",
    "        return Decimal(str(v))           # DynamoDB needs Decimal for numbers\n",
    "    if v is None:\n",
    "        return None\n",
    "    return v\n",
    "\n",
    "def batch_insert_to_dynamodb(table_name, pdf):\n",
    "    table = dynamodb.Table(table_name)\n",
    "    with table.batch_writer() as batch:\n",
    "        for _, row in pdf.iterrows():\n",
    "            item = {k: convert_value(v) for k, v in row.to_dict().items() if v is not None}\n",
    "            batch.put_item(Item=item)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 9. Example: Insert current aggregations\n",
    "\n",
    "Run periodically or in a job"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Get current state (for demo)\n",
    "electronics_current = spark.sql(\"SELECT * FROM electronics_agg\").toPandas()\n",
    "accessories_current = spark.sql(\"SELECT * FROM accessories_agg\").toPandas()   # if you created similar table\n",
    "furniture_current   = spark.sql(\"SELECT * FROM furniture_agg\").toPandas()\n",
    "\n",
    "batch_insert_to_dynamodb(\"Electronics\", electronics_current)\n",
    "batch_insert_to_dynamodb(\"Accessories\", accessories_current)\n",
    "batch_insert_to_dynamodb(\"Furniture\",   furniture_current)"

